  "Course Description": "This is a basic course in discrete mathematics, tailored for students in the computer science and applied math program. The course is intended to give students an exposure to formal mathematical language, the notion of proofs, and basic discrete structures such as graphs and permutations, as well as discrete probability and the probabilistic method.",
